    "excerpt": "If the status LED on your Axis Computer remains solid red after startup, it generally indicates a hardware initialization failure or an internal error. This often points to an issue with the basic hardware of the Axis computer itself. The specific meaning can vary slightly depending on the drive system (e.g., Drive System 04 or Drive System 09) of your ABB IRC5 controller. For both Drive System 04 and Drive System 09, a RED steady (forever) indicates the axis computer has failed to initialize basic hardware. The ABB IRC5 Operating/Troubleshooting Manual explicitly states that if the Axis computer's status LED remains red indefinitely, it likely requires replacement due to a permanent internal fault detected during self-test at start-up or an internal failure in the running system. The manual advises checking the power supply unit LED if an error like \"Logic Voltage to Drive Unit Error\" (39501) occurs, as a red LED there indicates an issue with the 24V supply. In summary, a persistent solid red status LED on an Axis Computer within an ABB IRC5 system is a strong indicator of a significant internal hardware failure. The most probable action, after confirming power and basic connections, is that the Axis computer unit itself may need to be replaced.",
    "confidence": 0.95
  }
]

